OL,6,FInflation has eased back to its
OL,7,Flowest level since March last year,
OL,8,Fbut remained higher than expected as
OL,9,Ffood prices continued to rise at a
OL,10,Fnear record pace.
OL,12,FThe Office for National Statistics
OL,13,F(ONS) said that Consumer Prices Index
OL,14,F(CPI) inflation fell to 8.7 per cent
OL,15,Fin April, down from 10.1 per cent in
OL,16,FMarch, as last year's energy price
OL,17,Fhikes were not repeated.
OL,19,FBut it was higher than forecast by
OL,20,Feconomists, who had pencilled in a
OL,21,Fdrop to 8.2 per cent in April.
OL,3,CInflation drops but food prices
OL,4,Cremain close to 45-year high
